JpTmtRtLIQdzts74sqKz2GBjNDYQRFxaKD8zg9x6DbXPqD_XcXshYqHSjNBSw3cVVm_WHMXnX7PacZcr8D3ep-BIPpXcZT8xWemdCgqMdP8dOrg4JAa5rbGQOT9V4l18Uiro5Ax9vbXRqETGlJMY4ZcVTq-w6rrHD_H8wVXdzg0l8eh4SzFPgqzL2GySNG22rb8ZrmClK5b6-BdOIe6A_J1EzkHOb17AodqmbSLuYyRAt22_75dayTcFEUpQYJDNFwZl2vXv5cZ_rPRlFeqIMUJdVA0fQ022df0TXfP-5qLi1xVKOYjt2ATpQyd1wA6dL6otXGJgDBe7-cWSYSQWCMNRB2c9F9SnoOrgf6TAasJIES3fjNQuFP4lY2n_PuStUqAIjg3B_IWv_FzBpe4m4H7UkrSpPiSE60RD8f7LFELc5IlJK20ggB3UWPYf6EPMeFbfmwDFSV_nfrvbXMzVFpzQH_yaxXFXUP9yxnGvN-L3SeZyNBWTDgsQgrdZ3HPROr52l0C-PoqATqHz7IjyDBDNt7X_1jXm58K2TIN7yXszr6JTgSAsnM932TlMaOuckHecCeCJ7F7hW3FLLHOW2LyKuoZ9WG066Ln52Ry7iMgUchMIixX7phAbUIyPmH9Nwp2p4pNtdS4j5dIPQkK5v5vxGf9uXB81n0gbblr-FGVgXt4jxWop9kYewszm8OGa_-zhQ2Fg5KZRB9hXMVvhhm-b2GQ1OqME9v3NcaQReuFFdNCqiBwaP6sNKE2w3FLzTL-FIH8bIAoEsGX88lYuJfEAV6l76yWbgYuctUfjtGBJYgfeMsqMK1vxGFcIg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing threading and dependencies**\\n\\nI'm considering a potential assertion on \\\"java.lang.Thread\\\" and checking the class name. It seems the testInstrumentation uses TestThread, and our callback is temporarily overridden during the instrumentation process before being restored, which is good. I wonder if the NativeImageSupport import adds a dependency, and I realize I might need the reactor-core dependency. The user asked for it, so using Reactor's scheduler could be more meaningful, but a custom predicate might work fine too. Should I install with loadIntegrations if I use the Reactor integration?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring instrumentation options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether to use ServiceLoader for instrumentation. It seems like BlockHound might have a built-in service for this? The main jar could possibly have META-INF/services, which is crucial. But then, what about custom markers with fewer dependencies? I wonder if the coverage class would remain active. It looks like install calls need to inject bootstrap classes before things become unsupported. If JDK instrumentation succeeds, then that seems promising. I need to edit my approach.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IYL0aLd8gxAUZlrgdoIM9joE|fc_0a8b60e43e2e40ac016a296dc950a88190ac14b2251b572afc", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/InstrumentationUtilsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_projectreactor_tools.blockhound;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch;\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\n\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport reactor.blockhound.BlockHound;\nimport reactor.blockhound.BlockingMethod;\n\npublic class InstrumentationUtilsTest {\n    @Test\n    void installInjectsBootstrapClassesAndDetectsBlockingCall() throws Exception {\n        CountDownLatch blockingCallDetected = new CountDownLatch(1);\n        AtomicReference<BlockingMethod> blockingMethod = new AtomicReference<>();\n\n        try {\n            BlockHound.builder()\n                    .nonBlockingThreadPredicate(current -> current.or(NonBlockingThread.class::isInstance))\n                    .blockingMethodCallback(method -> {\n                        blockingMethod.set(method);\n                        blockingCallDetected.countDown();\n                    })\n                    .install();\n        } catch (RuntimeException exception) {\n            if (hasUnsupportedFeatureError(exception)) {\n                return;\n            }\n            throw exception;\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedFeatureError(error);\n            return;\n        }\n\n        NonBlockingThread thread = new NonBlockingThread();\n        thread.start();\n        thread.join(TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMillis(5));\n        if (thread.isAlive()) {\n            thread.interrupt();\n            thread.join(TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMillis(1));\n        }\n\n        assertThat(thread.isAlive()).isFalse();\n        assertThat(thread.failure).isNull();\n        assertThat(blockingCallDetected.await(1, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(blockingMethod.get()).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(blockingMethod.get().getClassName()).isEqualTo(Thread.class.getName());\n        assertThat(blockingMethod.get().getName()).isEqualTo(\"sleep\");\n    }\n\n    private static boolean hasUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    private static void rethrowUnlessUnsupportedFeatureError(Error error) {\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class NonBlockingThread extends Thread {\n        private volatile Throwable failure;\n\n        @Override\n        public void run() {\n            try {\n                Thread.sleep(1);\n            } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n                failure = throwable;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1237, "output": 2357, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41482, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781099937634, "responseId": "resp_0a8b60e43e2e40ac016a296da22dfc8190b47aab5045eb1015"}}
