hound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/InstrumentationUtilsTest.java`\n\nWhat the test does:\n- Uses BlockHound’s public `BlockHound.builder()` API.\n- Installs BlockHound once in the test JVM, which reaches `InstrumentationUtils.injectBootstrapClasses(...)` and its `ClassLoader#getResourceAsStream(...)` call.\n- Configures a custom non-blocking thread predicate.\n- Triggers `Thread.sleep(...)` on that thread and verifies BlockHound reports the blocking method.\n- Handles Native Image unsupported-feature errors conservatively without skipping JVM execution.\n\nNotes:\n- `io.projectreactor:reactor-core:3.2.5.RELEASE` was already present in `build.gradle`, so no dependency edit was needed.\n- I did not run compile or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a8b60e43e2e40ac016a296e10a19481908a1d5e245c3e2b09\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1332, "output": 1346, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45686, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781100015286, "responseId": "resp_0a8b60e43e2e40ac016a296df0884c8190980733bcf737b41c"}, "toolResults": []}
